<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="title">Loading message</h3>
<p>In most cases the loader should have its own message or be in close proximity to one, like in the case of accompanying a button's label. In some cases it's appropriate to have a loader without a message.</p>
<h3 id="nesting">Nesting</h3>
<p>Loader inherits font properties, so when nested inside other elements like button, anchor, or headings it looks as you would expect it to.</p>
<h3 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h3>
<p>If a Loader doesn't have text it should use
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/ARIA_Techniques/Using_the_aria-labelledby_attribute" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><code>aria-labelledby</code></a>.</p>
